H0.text: Which President of the Philippines was deposed in 1986. Corazon Aquino

H1.text: Which President of the Philippines was deposed in 1986. Emilio Aguinaldo

H2.text: Which President of the Philippines was deposed in 1986. Manuel Quezon

H3.text: Which President of the Philippines was deposed in 1986. Marcos

A4.text: Allegations of mass electoral fraud, political turmoil, and human rights abuses led to the People Power Revolution of February 1986, which ultimately removed him from power.

A5.text: He was eventually deposed in 1986 by the People Power Revolution and was succeeded as president by Corazon Aquino.
